<p><b>Mamoru Oshii</b> (押井守 <i>Oshii Mamoru</i>; born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1951-08-08"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="08-08"><a href="/wiki/August_8" title="August 8">August 8</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1951" title="1951">1951</a></span> in <a href="/wiki/Tokyo" title="Tokyo">Tokyo</a>) is a <a href="/wiki/Japan" title="Japan">Japanese</a> <a href="/wiki/Filmmaker" title="Filmmaker" class="mw-redirect">filmmaker</a> and <a href="/wiki/Screenwriter" title="Screenwriter">writer</a> famous for his philosophy-oriented storytelling. Presently, Oshii lives in <a href="/wiki/Atami" title="Atami" class="mw-redirect">Atami</a>, <a href="/wiki/Shizuoka_Prefecture" title="Shizuoka Prefecture">Shizuoka prefecture</a>, Japan with his dogs – a <a href="/wiki/Basset_hound" title="Basset hound" class="mw-redirect">basset hound</a> named Gabriel (ガブリエル) and a <a href="/wiki/Mixed-breed_dog" title="Mixed-breed dog">mutt</a> named Daniel (both are featured in <i><a href="/wiki/Tachiguishi_Retsuden" title="Tachiguishi Retsuden" class="mw-redirect">Tachiguishi Retsuden</a></i>).</p>
<p>Oshii has stated his approach to directing is directly opposite the Hollywood formula, i.e. the visuals are the most important aspect, then the story and the characters come last.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
